name: Tirta Amerta
description: Amerta tells the story of Garuda, Dragon, and Turtle stirring the Ocean to get the water of immortality. Garuda, whose name is Jatayu, is the leader in the process of stirring the oceans and the Twin Dragons are in charge of turning the Giant Turtle. When the ocean water rotates very fast, Bhatara Vishnu appears who takes the water of immortality. So that the water is not abused by the giants.
